, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Catherine Iansdatter was born in 1360, in Membury, Devon, England, her father, Ian Christen Ivarssen, was 12 and her mother, Ingride Anne Ivarsdatter, was 12. She married William Ate Perye in 1386, in Devon, England. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 1 daughter. She died in 1420, in her hometown, at the age of 60."},"et":{"1360–1420":"1360–1420","1371–Female":"1371–Surnud","–Male":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1355–Male":"1355–Surnud","1362–1422":"1362–1422","1392–1451":"1392–1451","1380–1467":"1380–1467","1382–Female":"1382–Surnud","1348–Male":"1348–Surnud","1348–Female":"1348–Surnud","about 1382":"umbes 1382","1451":"1451","1362":"1362","1360":"1360","1382":"1382","1371":"1371","1392":"1392","1380":"1380","1348":"1348","1467":"1467","1422":"1422","1355":"1355","1420":"1420","1386":"1386","Membury, Devon, England":"Membury, Devon, England","England":"England","Worsley, Lancashire, England":"Worsley, Lancashire, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fi":{"1360–1420":"1360–1420","1371–Female":"1371–Kuollut","–Male":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1355–Male":"1355–Kuollut","1362–1422":"1362–1422","1392–1451":"1392–1451","1380–1467":"1380–1467","1382–Female":"1382–Kuollut","1348–Male":"1348–Kuollut","1348–Female":"1348–Kuollut","about 1382":"noin 1382","1451":"1451","1362":"1362","1360":"1360","1382":"1382","1371":"1371","1392":"1392","1380":"1380","1348":"1348","1467":"1467","1422":"1422","1355":"1355","1420":"1420","1386":"1386","Membury, Devon, England":"Membury, Devon, England","England":"England","Worsley, Lancashire, England":"Worsley, Lancashire, England","Devon, England":"Devon, England"},"fr":{"1360–1420":"1360–1420","1371–Female":"1371–Décédée","